with a solar position and solar radiation time-series calculator; by [https://web.archive.org/web/20070525051436/http://www.ecy.wa.gov/programs/eap/models.html Greg Pelletier]\n* [http://www.astm.org/Standards/G173.htm ASTM Standard] for solar spectrum at ground level in the US (latitude ~37 degrees).\n* [http://apod.nasa.gov/apod/ap100627.html Detailed spectrum of the Sun] at [http://apod.nasa.gov/apod/archivepix.html Astronomy Picture of the Day].\n\n{{The Sun}}\n{{Natural resources}}\n{{Star}}\n{{Nature}}\n\n[[Category:Sun|Light]]\n[[Category:Atmospheric radiation]]\n[[Category:Climate forcing]]\n[[Category:Solar energy]]\n[[Category:Light sources]]\n[[Category:IARC Group 1 carcinogens]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1008:b15c:a577:9032:dd80:b99a:57ff", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunlight"}
{"title_page": "Tongai Mnangagwa", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Tongai Mnangagwa\n| office              = [[House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)|Member of the Parliament of Zimbabwe]]<br />for [[Harare South]]\n| predecessor         = [[Shadreck Mashayamombe]]\n| termstart           = 5 September 2018\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1978|02|10|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Zambia]]\n| spouse              = {{marriage|Gwendolyn Mnangagwa|2001}}\n| relations           = [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] <small>(uncle)</small><br />[[Auxilia Mnangagwa]] <small>(aunt)</small>\n| children            = 5\nJeremy Mnangagwa,\n\nJamie Mnangagwa,\n\nJamimah Mnangagwa,\n\nJayden Mnangagwa,\n\nJamilah Mnangagwa\n| alma_mater          = [[Harare Polytechnic]]\n| residence           = [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]]\n| party               = [[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n}}\n\n'''Tongai Mafidi Mnangagwa''' (born 10 February 1978) is a [[Zimbabwe]]an politician who currently serves as the [[House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)|Member of Parliament]] for the [[Harare South]] constituency. He is the nephew of President [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] and is the sole [[ZANU\u2013PF]] MP representing [[Harare Province]].\n\n== Early life and education ==\nMnangagwa was born on 10 February 1978 in [[Zambia]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parlzim.gov.zw/component/k2/hon-mnangagwa-tongai|title=Hon. Mnangagwa Tongai|last=|first=|date=|website=Parliament of Zimbabwe|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He moved to [[Zimbabwe]] as a young child, attending Haig Park Primary School in [[Harare]].<ref name=\":0\" /> He did his [[GCE Ordinary Level|O Levels]] at [[Gokomere High School]], a [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[boarding school]] in [[Masvingo Province]], before completing his [[secondary education]] at [[Prince Edward School]], a [[State school|government]] [[Secondary school|high school]] in Harare.<ref name=\":0\" /> He then attended [[Harare Polytechnic]], where he earned a [[Academic certificate|certificate]] in [[marketing]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Political career ==\nMnangagwa joined [[ZANU\u2013PF]] at age 18, and became the youth chairperson for the party's Tangwena District at age 20.<ref name=\":0\" /> Later, he moved to [[Harare South]] and joined the party's Leopold Takawira District as a committee member, later rising to become the [[political commissar]] of the main board.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2018, Mnangagwa was ZANU\u2013PF's candidate for the House of Assembly in the 2018, running against over a dozen other candidates.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.zbc.co.zw/2018-elections-national-assembly-results/|title=2018 Elections: National Assembly Results|last=|first=|date=|website=ZBC News|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-11-30}}</ref> On election day, Mnangagwa won with a 39% [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]], defeating the two [[MDC Alliance]] candidates, [[incumbent]] [[Shadreck Mashayamombe]], and Tichaona Saurombe, who received 24% and 12%, respectively, as well as the [[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Tsvangirai|MDC\u2013T]] candidate, [[Desmond Jambaya]], who earned 6% of the vote.<ref name=\":1\" /> He was sworn into Parliament on 5 September 2018.\n\n== Personal life ==\nMnangagwa is married and lives in the [[Mabelreign, Harare|Mabelreign]] suburb of Harare.<ref name=\":0\" /> He has four children with his wife, Gwendolyn Mnangagwa.\n\n== Electoral history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"5\" |[[2018 Zimbabwean general election|2018 election]], [[Harare South]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Candidate\n!Party\n!Votes\n!%\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{ZANU-PF/meta/color}}\" |\n|'''Tongai Mnangagwa'''\n|[[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |24,503\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |39.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Shadreck Mashayamombe]]\n|[[MDC Alliance]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |21,363\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |34.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|Tichaona Saurombe\n|[[MDC Alliance]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |7,868\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |12.6\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|Desmond Jambaya\n|[[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Tsvangirai|MDC\u2013T]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |4,016\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |6.4\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Robson Kazetete\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1,829\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |2.9\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#2B3B90\" |\n|Tatenda Chigwada\n|[[People's Rainbow Coalition|PRC]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |679\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1.1\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#000000\" |\n|Spencer Chiwanika\n|[[National Patriotic Front (Zimbabwe)|NPF]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |620\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1.0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Elliot Piki\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |393\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.6\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Nathan Nyambuya\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |325\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.5\n|-\n|\n|Hearvy Ndagurwa\n|[[Zimbabwe Partnership for Prosperity|ZIPP]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |189\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Maxwell Munondo\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |151\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n|\n|Gaylord Kurisa\n|Build Zim Alliance\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |150\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#95C322\" |\n|Runwork Mharadze\n|[[National Constitutional Assembly|NCA]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |142\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Super Tanyiswa\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |136\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:right\" |'''Total'''\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |62,364\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:left\" |Source:<ref name=\":1\" />\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of members of the 9th Parliament of Zimbabwe]]\n\n== References ==\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mnangagwa, Tongai}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Zimbabwean politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Zimbabwean politicians]]\n[[Category:Harare Polytechnic alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)]]\n[[Category:People from Harare]]\n[[Category:Zambian emigrants to Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:ZANU\u2013PF politicians]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean businesspeople]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Tongai Mnangagwa\n| office              = [[House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)|Member of the Parliament of Zimbabwe]]<br />for [[Harare South]]\n| predecessor         = [[Shadreck Mashayamombe]]\n| termstart           = 5 September 2018\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1978|02|10|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Zambia]]\n| spouse              = {{marriage|Gwendolyn Mnangagwa|2001}}\n| relations           = [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] <small>(uncle)</small><br />[[Auxilia Mnangagwa]] <small>(aunt)</small>\n| children            = 5\nJeremy Mnangagwa,\n\nJamie Mnangagwa,\n\nJamimah Mnangagwa,\n\nJayden Mnangagwa,\n\nJamilah Mnangagwa\n| alma_mater          = [[Harare Polytechnic]]\n| residence           = [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]]\n| party               = [[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n}}\n\n'''Tongai Mafidi Mnangagwa''' (born 10 February 1978) is a [[Zimbabwe]]an politician who currently serves as the [[House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)|Member of Parliament]] for the [[Harare South]] constituency. He is the nephew of President [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] and is the sole [[ZANU\u2013PF]] MP representing [[Harare Province]].\n\n== Early life and education ==\nMnangagwa was born on 10 February 1978 in [[Zambia]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parlzim.gov.zw/component/k2/hon-mnangagwa-tongai|title=Hon. Mnangagwa Tongai|last=|first=|date=|website=Parliament of Zimbabwe|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He moved to [[Zimbabwe]] as a young child, attending Haig Park Primary School in [[Harare]].<ref name=\":0\" /> He did his [[GCE Ordinary Level|O Levels]] at [[Gokomere High School]], a [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[boarding school]] in [[Masvingo Province]], before completing his [[secondary education]] at [[Prince Edward School]], a [[State school|government]] [[Secondary school|high school]] in Harare.<ref name=\":0\" /> He then attended [[Harare Polytechnic]], where he earned a [[Academic certificate|certificate]] in [[marketing]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Political career ==\nMnangagwa joined [[ZANU\u2013PF]] at age 18, and became the youth chairperson for the party's Tangwena District at age 20.<ref name=\":0\" /> Later, he moved to [[Harare South]] and joined the party's Leopold Takawira District as a committee member, later rising to become the [[political commissar]] of the main board.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2018, Mnangagwa was ZANU\u2013PF's candidate for the House of Assembly in the 2018, running against over a dozen other candidates.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.zbc.co.zw/2018-elections-national-assembly-results/|title=2018 Elections: National Assembly Results|last=|first=|date=|website=ZBC News|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-11-30}}</ref> On election day, Mnangagwa won with a 39% [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]], defeating the two [[MDC Alliance]] candidates, [[incumbent]] [[Shadreck Mashayamombe]], and Tichaona Saurombe, who received 24% and 12%, respectively, as well as the [[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Tsvangirai|MDC\u2013T]] candidate, [[Desmond Jambaya]], who earned 6% of the vote.<ref name=\":1\" /> He was sworn into Parliament on 5 September 2018.\n\n== Personal life ==\nMnangagwa is married and lives in the [[Mabelreign, Harare|Mabelreign]] suburb of Harare.<ref name=\":0\" /> He has four children with his wife, Gwendolyn Mnangagwa.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailynews.co.zw/articles/2017/06/06/mnangagwa-nephew-dragged-to-court|title=Mnangagwa nephew dragged to court|last=Machakaire|first=Tarisai|date=2017-06-06|work=DailyNews Live|access-date=2018-11-30}}</ref> He is the nephew of President [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] and First Lady [[Auxillia Mnangagwa]].<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Electoral history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"5\" |[[2018 Zimbabwean general election|2018 election]], [[Harare South]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Candidate\n!Party\n!Votes\n!%\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{ZANU-PF/meta/color}}\" |\n|'''Tongai Mnangagwa'''\n|[[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |24,503\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |39.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Shadreck Mashayamombe]]\n|[[MDC Alliance]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |21,363\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |34.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|Tichaona Saurombe\n|[[MDC Alliance]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |7,868\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |12.6\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Movement for Democratic Change/meta/color}}\" |\n|Desmond Jambaya\n|[[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Tsvangirai|MDC\u2013T]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |4,016\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |6.4\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Robson Kazetete\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1,829\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |2.9\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#2B3B90\" |\n|Tatenda Chigwada\n|[[People's Rainbow Coalition|PRC]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |679\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1.1\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#000000\" |\n|Spencer Chiwanika\n|[[National Patriotic Front (Zimbabwe)|NPF]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |620\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |1.0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Elliot Piki\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |393\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.6\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Nathan Nyambuya\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |325\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.5\n|-\n|\n|Hearvy Ndagurwa\n|[[Zimbabwe Partnership for Prosperity|ZIPP]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |189\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.3\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Maxwell Munondo\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |151\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n|\n|Gaylord Kurisa\n|Build Zim Alliance\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |150\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#95C322\" |\n|Runwork Mharadze\n|[[National Constitutional Assembly|NCA]]\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |142\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Super Tanyiswa\n|Independent\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |136\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |0.2\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:right\" |'''Total'''\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |62,364\n| style=\"text-align:right\" |\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:left\" |Source:<ref name=\":1\" />\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of members of the 9th Parliament of Zimbabwe]]\n\n== References ==\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mnangagwa, Tongai}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Zimbabwean politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Zimbabwean politicians]]\n[[Category:Harare Polytechnic alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)]]\n[[Category:People from Harare]]\n[[Category:Zambian emigrants to Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:ZANU\u2013PF politicians]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean businesspeople]]\n", "name_user": "Alexiotawonazuze", "label": "safe", "comment": "removed a reference", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tongai_Mnangagwa"}
